reviews.title: OMG.. Where have they been all my life?
reviews.review_text: I have never eaten apples as much as I do now. The first bite had me hooked. I put them in the refrigerator for an even better treat. You'll love them. I can't believe I'm 55 years old and never knew an apple could be so juicy and sweet. When you take a bite, be prepared for the juices to start sprouting out everywhere. Seriously.. you might want to keep a safe distance from people. It's better to be safe than sorry. Also, it would be wise to have a paper towel or napkin handy. These fresh honeycrisp apples are definitely worth the extra money. You'll never like another one better, and you might even start to crave them. Yes, these mouth-watering apples are that good!

reviews.title: Three bad apples
reviews.review_text: The apples substituted had three rotted apples in the bag, which as the adage goes, makes the price even more expensive for the amount of edible apples left.

reviews.title: Bag of apples damages
reviews.review_text: i have pictures.. 2 apples had a cut mark or bite mark across them %26 2 others were badly bruised. that's 4 out of the 10 apples in the bag.. Almost half damaged... I've never received a bag of apples like this.. i but this item oftem... 😡😤

reviews.title: Mixed bag, buy at your own risk
reviews.review_text: Can be a mixed bag, sorry for pun. Some bags are great with a nice selection of apples. Others have damaged or close to rotten fruit in them. I always place the bag in the crisper so the fruit is chilled. Just wish there was a better way to check the quality before buying.

reviews.title: 95% of apples are bruised
reviews.review_text: I buy this product every week and I have WalMart Plus so they shop and delivery and every week 95% of the apples are bruised. There’s no quality inspection after the groceries are retrieved/before being delivered. Although, it could be bruised durning transportation. I’ve dealt with this issue for 2 yrs and still no resolution on their end. I guess it’s time to give up on WalMart and start using Kroger.

reviews.title: usually good. this time...rotten. literally.
reviews.review_text: we usually love these apples and we rarely have issues with quality in the store. however, today the person that picked the order did not look at the condition of the apples and when arriving home, they are rotten. the fact that the picker didnt check the quality is disappointing. they sold rotten apples to someone with 0 concern. i cant even return them due to the distance between my home and the store. this is gross and im definitely not holding onto apples for almost a month until my next trip there.

reviews.title: some apples might be going bad inside first.
reviews.review_text: used to have one or 2 apples bad in a bag now theres more. I found technically 5 apples bad in the last bag i bought and one was moldy from the core first. my daughter just ate what i thought was the best apple in the bag and it turns out the core is going bad luckily it was a small spot show she didnt eat the bad part

reviews.title: all bad
reviews.review_text: Every apple was brown and mushy. i was able to salvage one singular apple. its still pretty bruised though. you could easily see the worst ones from outside the bag. there was even juice in the bottom of the bag they were so far gone. the poctures show all different apples

reviews.title: Very disappointed
reviews.review_text: These apples were the worst, i bought them for my grandson, they were all bruised had brown spots on all of them. Seems as thought the shopper just grabbed a bag without bothering to check them. They should make sure customers are getting decent produce.

reviews.title: Apples were in terrible condition
reviews.review_text: 7 out of 11 apples in this 3 lb. bag were BAD -- there were 3 GOOD ONES. The 7 were bruised so much that a couple even looked like they were starting to rot. This is unacceptable and was not only the picker's fault for at least glancing through the clear bag, it was the produce employee's fault who seemed to be throwing the apple bags into the bins instead of placing them there.

my preferred apple but last couple of orders of these, the apples lacked the usual taste and skin had soft dark spots, same thing with my last a orders of envy apples, they were smaller, skin was wrinkled, lacked taste and crunch, maybe a seasonal problem but very disappointing and these 3lb. bags ain't cheap.

I am very disappointed with this item! At least three apples in the bag were completely rotten!! Next time I will get a ride to do my own shopping because I am handicapped and disabled, I asked a friend to do a pickup for me, but having Walmart shop for my produce was a mistake I will not make again. Sorry for the bad review, but this should not happen! Regards Jim

reviews.title: Rotten Produce
reviews.review_text: I was given a bag of apples in my pickup order where at least half of the apples were totally rotten. I don't mean that they had bruises...they were so rotten that when I took the apple bag out of the Walmart bag, stinky juice ran out of both bags and apples could be seen, from ten feet away, that were so long rotten they had collapsed on other apples in the bag. The person who answered the phone in the online order department was very apologetic and helpful in getting my refund but while the person who picked the order for me should pay much better attention to the quality of the produce they choose, Walmart of Russellville bears some blame in keeping such a poor watch over the produce they are offering customers. These apples didn't go this bad overnight. They have been sitting in a produce bin rotting more and more for days. In the picture, note the juice in the corner of the bag and the rotten apple squashed on top of the bottom apple. There are at least 6 more apples in the bag that are in various stages of totally rotten.
i took pictures of them they are all rotton. i paid between 7-8 bucks for these im not very happy about it. i usually find everything just fine but this was really awful

reviews.title: Bad Apples
reviews.review_text: Apple quality has gone way down. And the price has gone way up. Can't justify the new price when the apples are bruised and rotten! Honey Crisp apples should have a much longer shelf life!

reviews.title: The Best
reviews.review_text: I love honeycrisp apples and always keep them on hand. They stay mostly fresh in the fridge for a long time. The only negative is the price. But I guess all fruits have gone up quite a lot in the past few years. But always delicious and juicy. My favorite!

With fruit you're not always getting what you expect. As for fruit is concerned, I plan on going to Walmart myself; everyone has different ideas when it comes to choosing fruit. No worries. Walmart still has many great opportunities for the consumer.

reviews.title: Best apples EVER!!!
reviews.review_text: Apples are SO EXPENSIVE right now and this is the BEST APPLE in our opinion that there is!!! Always firm and crispy, just like an apple should be!!! I use them for baking as well as a snack!!! This handy bag is so nice, it's less expensive also!! Buying them as a single apple, I would get maybe 2 for the price of this entire bag!!! Plus, they're all about the same size and I would THINK came from the same orchard!!! Thanks for offering this item!!

reviews.title: Sad!
reviews.review_text: Very disappointed …we've had Honey Crisp apples from Sam's club many times. Bought them from Walmart because they were a little cheaper, but mainly because Walmart is much closer than Sam's club. Too many of them were bad. I'm not surprised by a bruise or two, but hate biting into an apple and it's mostly brown. I'll pay a few more cents and drive a bit to get good apples!

this bag is my go to. i appreciate a bulk size honeycrisp option. however, i wish the pick up shoppers paid more attention to the quality of the apples. this time i had one completely rotten. but the rest were in pristine condition, maybe they just missed it.

reviews.title: Last year's Season - a 4 out of 5
reviews.review_text: It is apparent that we are coming to the end of last year's apple season. However, these apples are more crisp than other's I have ordered in the last two months. But the flavor is not as fresh as what a new season picking would be. The skins are a bit tough almost as if they have been picked up from the ground, not freshly picked from a tree. But I have been cutting them up into slices and my dog is happy about them. Me, not so much.

reviews.title: Expensive!
reviews.review_text: I used to love buying these apples until the price went up drastically recently at over $8 for a 3 lb bag of apples is absolutely ridiculous when I can get a 5 lb bag of Red Delicious apples at a much lower price so I would save you the trouble with buying these.

honeycrisp used to be my favorite Apple until I start getting apples that were completely dry. so that's one I found Cosmo apples. they are more crunchier more juicier but don't get me wrong. some of the honeycrisp apples are the same way as Cosmo apples, crunchy and juicy

reviews.title: DELIVERY IN A HURRY
reviews.review_text: I just love food delivered, but, delivery folks are very nice but don't read the delivery instructions, I'm guessing because they're in a big hurry coming and going. They would save time if they just read and followed a couple simple worded directions, but thanks all the same.

reviews.title: Always damaged
reviews.review_text: I always get these and I end up throwing about 2-4 because they are damaged. Always risky buying fresh fruits while letting someone pick them out. I'm not sure if they are selling them damaged in the store or if the buyer smashed them in the cart or if the driver damaged them. But they ALWAYS come damaged.

These are the best apples available anywhere. Unfortunately, even though I ordered 1 bag, 8 bags were delivered! After an HOUR of searching who to complain to, i "talked" to an AI "person" who gave me credit for the entire 8 bags. Im not sure how the order got entered incorrectly in their computer, but it was not my fault.

reviews.title: The best apples HANDS DOWN!!
reviews.review_text: Honey crisp apples are amazing! They are so flavorful and the crispy bite you get each and every time you bite into it is top notch! There are quite literally no other apple I will purchase and consume other than Honey crisp apples! I can tell you that if you have yet to experience these type of apples....you are definitely missing out and should be adding these to your cart immediately!! Enjoy!!

I recently picked up a bag of grocery store apples, and unfortunately, they didn't live up to expectations. Here's a quick breakdown: The apples were noticeably smaller than average, which isn't a dealbreaker on its own—but it did raise eyebrows. They also looked overly ripe, with some showing soft spots and blemishes right out of the bag. Flavor was lacking. Instead of the bright, sweet-tart punch you'd expect from a good apple, these tasted dull and flat. There was none of that refreshing crispness that makes apples such a satisfying snack. These apples felt like they were past their prime before they even hit the shelf. If you're after quality produce, you might want to skip this bag and opt for picking apples individually—or better yet, visit a local orchard or farmers market.

reviews.title: Literally a mixed bag, either great or terrible!
reviews.review_text: When you get a bag of these apples that's good, they are the best apple I've ever tasted. But when they are not good, they are terrible! I buy a bag just about every two weeks. They can taste like the earth, literally like dirt or moldy or like a fermented wine. When they are at their best they have such a fresh, juicy, crisp sweet taste I love. I wish they were more consistent and the pricing is all over the place too. Last bag two weeks ago was $6 today was almost $10 and unfortunately not tasting the best.

reviews.title: One Bad Apple…
reviews.review_text: ….Spoils the bunch! Look what I found in our bag!!! Part of (not even the full apple) a rotten apple. The rest were coated in a moldy slime that this nasty CHUNK dispersed. The whole bag is in the trash. Never getting “fresh” items delivered from Walmart again. Shelf stable items only. Because how did nobody notice this?!?

I ordered apples but did not think that they would be brused beyond eating. I will ve returning rhese for a full refund. These are the most disgusting apples. I can not believe these were even brought to my car, as they are not even good enough to eat.

reviews.title: 1 Bad Apple, huh, try 7!
reviews.review_text: My $10 bag of apples only had two that were not bruised and rotten. I have bought several bags of these honey crisp. The first couple were high quality, but the last three that I have received have gotten progressively worse. My bananas haven't been much better. You might want to have your QC team check them closer before accepting them.

reviews.title: Honey crisp are great!
reviews.review_text: I would prefer to get The bigger individual Honeycrisp apples. I order online, And every time I order the bigger apples, they send me Gala apples, but charge me the Honeycrisp price. So I just buy a bag of apples and have my daughter occasionally get me the bigger ones at another grocery store.

reviews.title: MAGA- Make Apples Great Again
reviews.review_text: I've noticed apples in bags are either already bad or they go bad within a day or two. Doesn't matter which way they're stored…I've stored in a bowl out in the open, and stored in the fridge (last longer in fridge). I like buying a few of the single apples but those are crazy expensive nowadays!!

reviews.title: Honeycrisp apples
reviews.review_text: My family loves apples, for snacks and I make a lot of apple desserts. These honeycrisp apples have skyrocketed in price and went down in quality just in the last year. No bag of apples ground here in the states should cost 8 dollars a bag! Especially when other bags of apples cost 3-4 dollars. Mind blowing.

reviews.title: So Sweet🍎🍏
reviews.review_text: I am a huge fan of Honeycrisp apples, and for good reason. The name says it all -they have an unbeatable crunch that you can hear with every bite, and a flood of juice follows. The flavor is a masterpiece, a beautiful blend of honeyed sweetness with a refreshing hint of acidity that keeps you coming back for more. Whether I'm eating one fresh or slicing it for a salad, it's consistently the best apple I've ever had. Truly a premium apple that's worth every penny.

I love ordering online and I have never been disappointed. Always on time. They are great about picking out the crispness and size of the fruits and vegetables They are also very careful about how they put it in your vehicle always with a smile. Good job.

reviews.title: No Refund for Rotting Fruit
reviews.review_text: My entire bag of apples was inedible. Every single apple was bruised, cracked and rotting. I contacted support for a refund and the refund was pending return of the gross fruit. I live 40 minutes away from the store and only go once a week so I was unable to return the rotting bag of apples and get a refund.

they were so bruised and punctured, I had to make apple sauce. there were no other options. it was like they played catch with the apples in a gravel road and missed catching them on purpose. honestly losing hope in Walmart. every dept is changing and not all of it is for the best.

reviews.title: Fresh, Juicy, and Perfectly Crisp!
reviews.review_text: The 3-pound bag of Honeycrisp apples from Walmart is fresh, crisp, and perfectly sweet-tart! Every apple is juicy with great crunch, and they stay fresh for days. A perfect convenient choice for snacking or lunches! My son could eat these all day long! Highly recommend!

reviews.title: Was this bag of apples used to ward off an attack?
reviews.review_text: Out of this 3 pound bag, exactly 3 apples were decent. The rest were gouged with deep bruising. 2 days on the counter and a swarm of fruit flies later, they're in the trash. So disappointed. Pictures only shows the last 5 I threw after noticing the fruit flies.

reviews.title: old apples
reviews.review_text: This bag of apples is OLD. Obviously old. wax is dull. when peeled lots of surface bruises like the bag has been tossed around for a month. Its not just one or two apples, so far every apple in the bag is old. I do delivery. I would not have picked this bag for myself.

How do you make the best apple taste more bland and sad than a red delicious? How? Why would you do this to people? It's mean. How long have y'all had these in cold storage? The worst honey crisp apple experience I've ever had. I cannot ever get back the time I wasted eating one of these AND I HAD HONEY ROASTED PEANUT BUTTER AND MARSHMALLOW FLUFF DIP. Did not help the nothingness of these apples. Ssshhhhaaaaaaaammmmmeeeee.

reviews.title: A few apples were spoiled/rotting had to discard
reviews.review_text: A few of the apples were spoiled; had to discard fruit. This was my 1st time using this shopping feature from Walmart. Not a good experience; most of the items I purchased were (fruit) which a lot had to be thrown away. I'm a truck driver ; I wasn't able to return product didn't check quality of merchandise until I arrived in next city.

the last few times I've bought fruit from Walmart pick up, my fruit had bruises and some had white mold. also when i buy ready made meals, they are past their expiration date. very disappointing. this has happened the last few times I've ordered food from Wal-Mart pick up.

I love honeycrisp apples and getting them in this bag is such a great deal. These apples in the bag are the perfect 1 person single for snacking. Sometimes you will see Honeycrisp in the store and they are HUGE and you cannot eat it all yourself. These are the perfect 1 person snack size. These apples are crisp, sweet, and tart all at the same time. It is like a gala and pink lady combined but even better.

reviews.title: Best eating apple
reviews.review_text: Very good eating apple/snack. Thin skin, crispy texture, sweet taste. It's now my favorite Apple haven't used any yet for cooking. Will try it in the future like the granny Smith for cooking. I definitely recommend if you just want to eat one as a snack

reviews.title: Not this time
reviews.review_text: I have ordered these apples in the past and have not had any problem, they were delicious. Unfortunately, this time around the apples I received were old, bruised and I immediately returned them! Obviously the associate that pick my order was not paying attention.

reviews.title: bad apples
reviews.review_text: We love these apples and always get them. However the quality is going down. We have been receiving apples with smaller bruises, however today our bag had 2 very bad apples. The entire bag was dripping and sticky. There is no way the person packing the order didn't realize it.

Walmart has carried these same apples for about 6 months. I have bought about 3 -4 bags since last fall or summer and they have been horrible. The apples are green and inedible. I actually tried making applesauce with them and it was inedible. Walmart needs to do better. I kept thinking the next shipment was going to be better but, the fool that I was, I bought them again, thinking they COULD NOT possibly be crappy again. There is no way Walmart should continue to buy something this sub-standard for such a prolonged period of time. This wasn’t just a one-off bad crop. Not recommended

reviews.title: An apple a day….
reviews.review_text: “An Apple 🍎 a day keeps the Doctor away..” I eat an apple or two per day. I absolutely love these HoneyCrisp apples. They are sweet, delicious and do have a “crispy texture.” They might be alittle more than other apples, but they are worth it and I will only purchase them.

reviews.title: Usually very good, this bag not so good
reviews.review_text: I've purchased several bags of these apples in the past and they've always been in great shape and very tasty! This bag not so good. Several of the apples have large bruises on them and the taste isn't crisp like it should be. The taste is a little more mush-like, kind of like applesauce.

reviews.title: Honeycrisp Apples
reviews.review_text: I have always loved Honeycrisp Apples. This was the second bag of these Honeycrisps I purchased from Walmart within the last month. Considering they're not in season, I was thrilled. They were surprisingly delicious, sweet, juicy, ripe, perfect color %26 good size. I'll continue to buy them.
seriously Walmart? these were less than $5 two weeks ago and now are over $7. other apples are not going up.

reviews.title: price jacking
reviews.review_text: stop f 1ng around. these are too small %26 bruised to be be be jumping from under $5 to over $7 in less than 2 weeks yall are f 1ng wild

Honeycrisp Apples is my number one choice. I happened to have try "Honeycrisp Apples" apples when visiting family members in GA. I've been hooked since. Thank you Walmart.com for keeping that product shocked. Sincerely, M

Never knew about rotisserie chicken I ordered being out of stock until order was delivered. If someone had contacted me I could have made a substitution. Shopper needs to contact the customer and let them decide on a substitute.
We love The bag of Honeycrisp apples that are just a nice small size. Our granddaughter says they're the best apples… she only eats apples at our house.

I have ordered these several times because they are so good. I am not happy with the poor quality and multiple large rotten spots that have to be cut out. There have been several that were so rotten they had to be thrown in the garbage.
These were sooooo bad %26 damaged and each and every apple was scared badly it wasn't minor and I was very upset about it and very surprised at how bad it was . :/ just like the avocados :|

reviews.title: Quality just not good any more
reviews.review_text: I have been buying Honeycrisp apples from walmart from long time but the price goes up and the quality gets worse. This time they didn't last long before rotting.

reviews.title: Small and bruised
reviews.review_text: Super small apples, and I don't know how they are handled but they will come bruised. Every bag there are a few that take a beating. Leaves juice spoiled and ruins those and makes a mess of things for the rest.

reviews.title: Rotten
reviews.review_text: One third of the apples were rotten literally to the core and half of the rest are showing signs of rotting already. I'll go back to Kroger where the fruit is amazing. Picture shows the good ones.
I love this apple but the quality of them has gone way down. Lots of byuising and mushy parts. Have to cut a lot of the apple away. Other tham that, love the flavor and texture.

The last three times I bought these over half of them were bruised and inedible. I even bought a bag in person instead of having them delivered with the same result. Honey Crisp is my favorite but I had to switch to a different brand.

reviews.title: Very Bad Quality
reviews.review_text: For paying over double what other apples cost, I was highly disappointed to find rotten apples with fermented juice in the bag. It was an online delivery so someone else did the shopping and neglected to inspect it first.

I've bought these a few times and each time half the bag has bruised apples. Honey crisp apples are the best imo. The ones that are good are great. I just hate that you spend that much money and they are damaged.

reviews.title: Rotten apples
reviews.review_text: The honey crisp apples I received in my pickup order were very rotten. I had to throw the entire bag out. I was reimbursed for the cost of the apples. Now I have to go back and buy more apples

reviews.title: juicy, crispy, and sweet apples
reviews.review_text: they're my husbands favorite apples and we get them from Walmart everytime. every once in a while one or two have a bruise but they're still delicious and refreshing snack.
Fruit at this Walmart is Horrible, not fresh and goes bad too soon. Fruit has no taste and appears rush-grown. I am looking to shop somewhere else at this point.

reviews.title: Bad Apples
reviews.review_text: I normally love Honey Crisp apples, but out of the 10 apples in the bag, seven were moldy and bruised. I salvaged three apples. I know I will not be purchasing fresh fruit or vegetables from Walmart anymore.

reviews.title: Weekly apple purchase
reviews.review_text: I get one bag a week or so. They are usually good although, sometimes I get a few rotten ones. Walmart is usually really good about refunding my for that. But here all the quality and taste of apples is good.

reviews.title: Mushy Honeycrisp apples.
reviews.review_text: Out of 10-11 apples in the bag 5 were mushy, and soft, bag was wet when delivered and these are expensive apples. Had to throw mushy apples in trash. Disappointed!

reviews.title: Rotten apples.
reviews.review_text: There was rotten apples in the bag and during transport I guess they had been squeezed and the rotten juice went all over my kitchen floor and me when I picked the walmart bag up.

reviews.title: Substitutions
reviews.review_text: The bag of apples that I wanted was substituted for these and they were overripe and some were rotten! I will stick with my Cosmetic Crisp from now on and except no substitute on my apples.
Several bags in a row had a rotten apple within. The entire bag was ruined and inedible. From now on I will order apples individually with the hopes that the worker will pay attention to the quality

reviews.title: Bad produce
reviews.review_text: I think they grabbed the worst bag of apples they saw. Apples were bruised and mushy. Very disappointed in the produce I received in my last order. One of the reasons I quit doing grocery. Pick up was because of the produce.
The apples I received were mushy and leaking everywhere. Absolutely awful that someone would pick that and think it was acceptable to pay $9 for apples that were was past edible.
There were a few rotten apples. So after weeding those out it is not worth it. Better off picking out single apples to ensure you get quality apples.
The best way to buy these delicious apples: They're small, ripe, and enough of them to last a while. The bigger ones are unripe, more expensive, yet go bad quickly. I kept throwing them out.

reviews.title: Honey crisp bag of apple
reviews.review_text: The bag was completely damaged. It's like the shopper. Didn't even look to see what was in it. Half the apples were terribly bruised when they arrived at my house.

reviews.title: Bruised apples
reviews.review_text: The only thing i dislike from a lot of it being delivered to me, is that a lot of the times, I don't get fresh produce. Many bags have had bruises on the apples. Very disappointing

reviews.title: mixed bag?
reviews.review_text: The price keeps going up, and the quality is going down. decided to splurge yesterday and pay the nearly $8, and highly suspect that they're not even all honeycrisp apples.

reviews.title: Bad apples
reviews.review_text: I understand produce has a limited shelf life but I just picked up my order and 4 out of 8 of the apples were bad. They had huge soft spots, one of the was almost half brown. so gross.

reviews.title: Every apple was fresh and crisp!
reviews.review_text: All the apples were good quality. After just receiving a bag of navel oranges and they all were bad, it was very important to write a review of these crisp apples that I'm still able to enjoy.

These apples are so delicious! They are the perfect size for a light snack or your child's school lunch. I was skeptical about buying a whole bag just for my husband and me, but they last so long that they never go bad.
These honeycrisp apples are one of my favorite Walmart finds. I have never seen honeycrisp apples of this quality available for this price on a regular basis.
I used to dislike eating red apples because they always tasted so blech, but Honey crisp isn't even fully red so maybe that's why it's so tasty! haha seriously my favorite apple ever

These were smaller than the ones you buy individually and that's exactly what I liked. They are just the right size for someone watching their sugar intake. They were fresh, unblemished and perfect. I will buy again!

reviews.title: Bad apples
reviews.review_text: Most of the apples in the bag were bruised or rotten. I had to throw some of them away. Very disappointing. Groceries are too expensive to have to throw away.

reviews.title: Honey crisp apple
reviews.review_text: They were pretty much all rotten. I wish the person that picked up the groceries for me would have taken the time to pick out a bag that was a lil better..

reviews.title: Poor and pitiful
reviews.review_text: These apples were left overs for sure. They were very irregular, some were bruised, not tangy, and skins were bitter. Not at all up to Walmart standard of freshness.
I love these apples, but I was sent a bag full of bruised and punctured apples. Maybe one was edible the rest were trash. So sad it was like throwing money away.

reviews.title: One rotten apple
reviews.review_text: I have been ordering these apples for a long time and been happy. This time every Apple was so badly bruised that I couldn't eat it. It was a total waste of money!

reviews.title: Applelicious
reviews.review_text: Apples are great as a snack with peanut butter or cheese slices or as a healthy dessert after a meal. And they are of course healthy for you. I prefer honey crisp even over pink lady apples.

reviews.title: Small and bruised apples, save your money!
reviews.review_text: The apples were everyone of them bruised and it didnt show the bruising until the next day. Pricey apples to be able to use them. Small apples this ti., normally big apples but ot this time

reviews.title: Great taste, poor quality.
reviews.review_text: 3 out of the last 4 bags of Honeycrisp apples have had at least 4 poor-quality apples. They are delicious apples, but the quality seems to be declining.

reviews.title: Our Favorite Apple!
reviews.review_text: The Honey-crisp Apples are some of the sweetest apples I've ever tasted. We like to dice an apple up and add it to a bowl of non-fat yogurt for a quick snack! Tasty treat!

i love these apples. crazy expensive for an apple but theyre big(the singles. the bagged one are a lot smaller.) the apple in general are amazing. i love that i can get all the things i get delivered or picked up.

This is the second time and the apples are seriously bruised..doesn't anyone watch quality especially the high price for 8 apples..last time it was the same except i only had 7 apples and a hug bite was taken out of one gross

reviews.title: Usually the best.
reviews.review_text: For how much these cost I shouldn't have one bad apple let alone one bad spot. The last three times I've bought honeycrisp they are mainly all banged up and not worth the $$

reviews.title: Don't buy it!!!
reviews.review_text: I should have taken the advice from the reviews I read. I guess I found out for myself. Don't buy them apples. Looks like someone bit into it. Literal teeth marks and some are soft.

reviews.title: Toothpaste
reviews.review_text: Yes I ordered the crest toothpaste one 1️⃣ single pack of toothpaste, but I got a three pack toothpaste and I would like to know why you sent me three instead of the one I ordered. Thank you!!! be blessed.🙏🏽😊🙏🏽

reviews.title: Delicious Apples
reviews.review_text: Great apples at a wonderful price. Just like any other brand, you will sometimes get some bruised apples. For the majority of the time, they are crisp and delicious.
The only problem with buying produce online: You never know if you're getting fresh or nearly rotten, because the shoppers don't care and apparently Walmart doesn't care if you get fresh produce.

reviews.title: Great fiber filled snack
reviews.review_text: Honeycrisp apples are just as the name says. They are crisp, sweet, and have a nice amount of juice in them. My husband loves them, and I love the fact that they are a healthy snack full of fiber.

reviews.title: Unsightly apples
reviews.review_text: Usually these apples are great - delicious, crisp, quality. However today several had black spots on them - not soggy, but unsightly. Very unappetizing, so not worth the usual price for honey crisp apples.

reviews.title: Very fresh!
reviews.review_text: My son loves these! And I do too. They're really crisp and fresh. My husband thinks that they're a little sour, but he is picky lol. They're really good!

reviews.title: Not examined

reviews.title: Rotten and dripping

My family loves these honey crisp apples. I buy 1-2 bags a week. Between the 5 of us we eat around an apple a day. And with Walmart I can have it delivered straight to my door, they even put all cold or frozen stuff in our fridge in the garage, at no extra cost. They can’t even accept tips. Our most frequent %26 favorite delivery associate is SUSAN…we LOVE SUSAN!!! She’s practically a part of our family…it weren’t for her we wouldn’t have any food. Jk LOL. They very rarely deliver anything broken, bruised, out of date, etc. And Susan brings the best fruit. We have a fruit stand right down the road that we shop from frequently. And sometimes the fruit from Walmart is better…sometimes. But these apples are always sooo good. Thank you Walmart %26 thank you SUSAN! 💙
